Uses of Class
org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractTreeNode

Packages that use AbstractTreeNode
org.sbml.jsbml Pure Java implementation of the data structures to represent all SBML constructs. 
org.sbml.jsbml.util A collection of handy utilities when working with JSBML classes, such as classes for String manipulation or mathematical operations. 
org.sbml.jsbml.xml This package provides classes and methods to deal with SBML in form of XML elements, i.e., here you can find parsers and writers for SBML and also elements to define XML nodes to be used for notes or annotations.

 class TreeNodeAdapter
           This class is a wrapper element for any Object that should be linked into a tree data structure as represented by AbstractTreeNode, but that might by itself not be an instance of TreeNode, i.e., not compatible with the remaining tree data structure.
